        "content": "<p>I found an issue what I believe is the NVIDIA proprietary driver. Here is an error I can see in the logs for example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">NVRM</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">GPU0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nvAssertFailedNoLog</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Assertion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">pEntries</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NULL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gmmu_walk</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">828</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What would be the best way to approach it?<br>\nMy GPU </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"mi\">01</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mf\">00.0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VGA</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">controller</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">NVIDIA</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Corporation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GA104</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Geforce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RTX</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3070</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ti</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Laptop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GPU</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><